# Radio

Radio buttons are for making an individual selection from a list of multiple options.
Always have a default radio option selected, whichever is the most common choice for users.

## Installation & Import

```bash
yarn add @ids-ts/radio
```

```tsx
import { Radio, RadioGroup } from '@ids-ts/radio';
```

## Props API

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `checked` | `boolean` | No | Specifies whether the radio is checked. |
| `children` | `ReactNode | string` | No | The Radio label. |
| `description` | `ReactNode | string` | No | * Description text below the label |
| `disabled` | `boolean` | No | - |
| `name` | `string` | No | a name assign to the radio input |
| `size` | `'small' | 'medium'` | No | - |
| `onChange` | `RadioOnChangeType` | No | Callback function with customize event object that is fired when a Radio has been checked. |
| `value` | `string` | No | Radio current value. |
| `validationType` | `InlineValidationType` | No | - |
| `e` | `RadioOnChangeEventType): void` | Yes | - |
| `target` | `{ checked: boolean; value: string }` | Yes | Modified event target with radio value. |
| `value` | `string` | No | a event target value |

<details>
<summary>Full TypeScript Interface</summary>

```typescript
export interface RadioProps
  extends Omit<ThemeableElement<'input'>, 'size' | 'onChange' | 'type'> {
  /** Specifies whether the radio is checked. */
  checked?: boolean;
  /** The Radio label. */
  children?: ReactNode | string;
  /**
   * Description text below the label
   */
  description?: ReactNode | string;
  /**
   * Disable the Radio.
   *
   * @default false
   */
  disabled?: boolean;
  /** a name assign to the radio input */
  name?: string;
  /** Affects size of text rendered next to checkbox
   *
   * @default 'medium'
   *
   */
  size?: 'small' | 'medium';
  /** Callback function with customize event object that is fired when a Radio has been checked.  */
  onChange?: RadioOnChangeType;
  /** Radio current value. */
  value?: string;
  /**
   * Determines the type of Validation Message : ['error', 'warning', 'success', 'invalid', 'info', '']
   *
   * @default ''
   */
  validationType?: InlineValidationType;
}

export interface RadioOnChangeType {
  (e: RadioOnChangeEventType): void;
}

export interface RadioOnChangeEventType {
  /** a modify event target */
  target: {
    /** a event target check value */
    checked?: boolean;
    /** a event target value */
    value?: string;
  };
  stopPropagation?(): void;
  preventDefault?(): void;
}
```

</details>

