## Usage Patterns

### Basic

```tsx
() => (
  <RadioGroup
    label="Ready to learn more about IDS Radio Buttons?"
    name="numLabels"
    data-automation-id="globalRadio"
  >
    <Radio value="1" data-automation-id="basicRadio">
      Yes
    </Radio>
    <Radio value="2">No</Radio>
    <Radio value="3">Maybe</Radio>
  </RadioGroup>
)
```

### No Visible Label Use Aria Label For Accessibility

```tsx
() => (
  <>
    <RadioGroup
      aria-label="Did you find the feature helpful?"
      name="numLabels"
      data-automation-id="globalRadio"
    >
      <Radio value="1" data-automation-id="ariaRadio" aria-label="Yes">
        Yes
      </Radio>
      <Radio value="2">No</Radio>
      <Radio value="3">Maybe</Radio>
    </RadioGroup>
    <B2 as="p">
      The element is used to associate a text label with a form field. The label
      is used to tell users the value that should be entered in the associated
      input field. If your design does not include a visible label, then you
      must include an aria-label to provide information to the screen reader.
    </B2>
  </>
)
```

### Radio Group With Inline Validation Message

```tsx
() => (
  <>
    <RadioGroup
      label="Select your pizza crust type"
      name="errorlabels"
      validationType="error"
      validationMessage="Please make a selection before proceeding"
      style={{ marginBottom: 30 }}
    >
      <Radio value="1">Hand Tossed</Radio>
      <Radio value="2">Thin Crust</Radio>
      <Radio value="3">Gluten Free Crust</Radio>
    </RadioGroup>

    <RadioGroup
      label="Select your pizza sauce"
      name="warningLables"
      validationType="warning"
      validationMessage="Your pizza will not have any sauce since no selection has been made"
    >
      <Radio value="1">Marinara</Radio>
      <Radio value="2">Alfredo</Radio>
      <Radio value="3">Pesto</Radio>
    </RadioGroup>
  </>
)
```

